  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Big-Theta Notation Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 2em;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n    color: #333;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    color: #2c3e50;\n  }\n  section {\n    margin-bottom: 2em;\n  }\n  code {\n    background: #eee;\n    padding: 0.1em 0.3em;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    font-family: monospace;\n  }\n  .chart-container {\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    width: 100%;\n    max-width: 700px;\n    height: 350px;\n  }\n  canvas {\n    background: white;\n    border: 1px solid #ccc;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n  }\n  p.intro {\n    max-width: 700px;\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Big-Theta (&#x0398;) Notation Visualization</h1>\n\n<section>\n  <p class=\"intro\">\n    <strong>Big-Theta notation</strong> (&#x0398;) describes the tight asymptotic bound of an algorithm's running time or space usage. When we say:\n  </p>\n  <p><code>f(n) = &#x0398;(g(n))</code>,</p>\n  <p>it means f(n) grows proportionally to g(n) within constant factors for sufficiently large n. Formally, there exist positive constants c<sub>1</sub>, c<sub>2</sub>, and n<sub>0</sub> such that for all n ≥ n<sub>0</sub>:</p>\n  <p style=\"margin-left: 2em;\">\n    c<sub>1</sub> · g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c<sub>2</sub> · g(n)\n  </p>\n  <p>This means f(n) is bounded both above and below by g(n), up to constant multiples.</p>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>Example: f(n) = 3n + 5 and Big-Theta(n)</h2>\n  <p>\n    Consider the function <code>f(n) = 3n + 5</code>. We claim that <code>f(n) = &#x0398;(n)</code>. Let's visualize f(n) along with c<sub>1</sub>·n and c<sub>2</sub>·n for some constants to see the bounds.\n  </p>\n  <div class=\"chart-container\">\n    <canvas id=\"thetaChart\" width=\"700\" height=\"350\" aria-label=\"Big-Theta notation example chart\" role=\"img\"></canvas>\n  </div>\n  <p>\n    Blue line: <code>f(n) = 3n + 5</code><br />\n    Green line: lower bound <code>c<sub>1</sub>·n</code> (e.g., 2n)<br />\n    Red line: upper bound <code>c<sub>2</sub>·n</code> (e.g., 4n)\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>Try Your Own Function</h2>\n  <p>Input a linear function <code>f(n) = a*n + b</code> and constants to see if it fits within Big-Theta bounds of <code>g(n) = n</code>.</p>\n  <form id=\"functionForm\" aria-label=\"Big-Theta function input form\">\n    <label>\n      a (coefficient for n): \n      <input type=\"number\" step=\"any\" name=\"a\" value=\"3\" required />\n    </label>\n    <br/><br/>\n    <label>\n      b (constant term): \n      <input type=\"number\" step=\"any\" name=\"b\" value=\"5\" required />\n    </label>\n    <br/><br/>\n    <label>\n      c<sub>1</sub> (lower bound constant): \n      <input type=\"number\" step=\"any\" name=\"c1\" value=\"2\" required />\n    </label>\n    <br/><br/>\n    <label>\n      c<sub>2</sub> (upper bound constant): \n      <input type=\"number\" step=\"any\" name=\"c2\" value=\"4\" required />\n    </label>\n    <br/><br/>\n    <button type=\"submit\">Visualize</button>\n  </form>\n  <div class=\"chart-container\" style=\"margin-top:1em;\">\n    <canvas id=\"userChart\" width=\"700\" height=\"350\" aria-label=\"User input Big-Theta example chart\" role=\"img\"></canvas>\n  </div>\n  <p id=\"resultText\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\"></p>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n  // Utility function to draw lines on canvas for given function f, color, and label on the right edge\n  function drawLine(ctx, func, nMax, color, label, yScale, xScale) {\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.strokeStyle = color;\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n    for (let n = 0; n <= nMax; n++) {\n      let x = n * xScale;\n      let y = yScale - func(n) * yScale / nMax;\n      if (n === 0) {\n        ctx.moveTo(x, y);\n      } else {\n        ctx.lineTo(x, y);\n      }\n    }\n    ctx.stroke();\n\n    // Label at right side\n    ctx.fillStyle = color;\n    ctx.font = \"14px Arial\";\n    let lastX = nMax * xScale + 5;\n    let lastY = yScale - func(nMax) * yScale / nMax;\n    ctx.fillText(label, lastX, Math.min(yScale - 5, lastY));\n  }\n\n  function drawThetaExample() {\n    const canvas = document.getElementById(\"thetaChart\");\n    const ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\");\n    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n\n    // Axes\n    ctx.strokeStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n    ctx.beginPath();\n\n    // y-axis\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 10);\n    ctx.lineTo(40, 330);\n    // x-axis\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 330);\n    ctx.lineTo(690, 330);\n\n    ctx.stroke();\n\n    // Arrows\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 10);\n    ctx.lineTo(35, 20);\n    ctx.lineTo(45, 20);\n    ctx.closePath();\n    ctx.fillStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.fill();\n\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(690, 330);\n    ctx.lineTo(680, 325);\n    ctx.lineTo(680, 335);\n    ctx.closePath();\n    ctx.fill();\n\n    // Axis Labels\n    ctx.font = \"14px Arial\";\n    ctx.fillStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.fillText(\"0\", 30, 340);\n    ctx.fillText(\"n\", 680, 350);\n    ctx.fillText(\"f(n)\", 10, 20);\n\n    const offsetX = 40;\n    const offsetY = 330;\n    const nMax = 100;\n    const xScale = (canvas.width - offsetX - 20) / nMax; // horizontal scale\n    const yScale = offsetY - 10; // vertical scale\n\n    // Functions\n    function f(n) { return 3 * n + 5; }\n    function lowerBound(n) { return 2 * n; }\n    function upperBound(n) { return 4 * n; }\n\n    // Draw lower bound\n    ctx.save();\n    ctx.translate(offsetX, 0);\n    drawLine(ctx, lowerBound, nMax, \"#27ae60\", \"Lower bound (2n)\", yScale, xScale);\n    drawLine(ctx, upperBound, nMax, \"#c0392b\", \"Upper bound (4n)\", yScale, xScale);\n    drawLine(ctx, f, nMax, \"#2980b9\", \"f(n) = 3n + 5\", yScale, xScale);\n    ctx.restore();\n  }\n\n  // For user input visualization\n  function drawUserFunction(a,b,c1,c2) {\n    const canvas = document.getElementById(\"userChart\");\n    const ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\");\n    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n\n    // Axes\n    ctx.strokeStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n    ctx.beginPath();\n\n    // y-axis\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 10);\n    ctx.lineTo(40, 330);\n    // x-axis\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 330);\n    ctx.lineTo(690, 330);\n\n    ctx.stroke();\n\n    // Arrows\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(40, 10);\n    ctx.lineTo(35, 20);\n    ctx.lineTo(45, 20);\n    ctx.closePath();\n    ctx.fillStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.fill();\n\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(690, 330);\n    ctx.lineTo(680, 325);\n    ctx.lineTo(680, 335);\n    ctx.closePath();\n    ctx.fill();\n\n    // Axis Labels\n    ctx.font = \"14px Arial\";\n    ctx.fillStyle = \"#555\";\n    ctx.fillText(\"0\", 30, 340);\n    ctx.fillText(\"n\", 680, 350);\n    ctx.fillText(\"f(n)\", 10, 20);\n\n    const offsetX = 40;\n    const offsetY = 330;\n    const nMax = 100;\n    const xScale = (canvas.width - offsetX - 20) / nMax; // horizontal scale\n    const yScale = offsetY - 10; // vertical scale\n\n    // Functions\n    function f(n) { return a * n + b; }\n    function lowerBound(n) { return c1 * n; }\n    function upperBound(n) { return c2 * n; }\n\n    // Draw lower bound\n    ctx.save();\n    ctx.translate(offsetX, 0);\n    drawLine(ctx, lowerBound, nMax, \"#27ae60\", `Lower bound (${c1}n)`, yScale, xScale);\n    drawLine(ctx, upperBound, nMax, \"#c0392b\", `Upper bound (${c2}n)`, yScale, xScale);\n    drawLine(ctx, f, nMax, \"#2980b9\", `f(n) = ${a}n + ${b}`, yScale, xScale);\n    ctx.restore();\n\n    // Check if f(n) is within bounds for n from n0 on (choosing n0=some small number)\n    let n0 = 10;\n    let fitsTheta = true;\n    for(let n = n0; n <= nMax; n++) {\n      const valF = f(n);\n      const lb = lowerBound(n);\n      const ub = upperBound(n);\n      if (valF < lb || valF > ub) {\n        fitsTheta = false;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n\n    return fitsTheta;\n  }\n\n  document.getElementById(\"functionForm\").addEventListener(\"submit\", function(e) {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    const form = e.target;\n    const a = parseFloat(form.a.value);\n    const b = parseFloat(form.b.value);\n    const c1 = parseFloat(form.c1.value);\n    const c2 = parseFloat(form.c2.value);\n\n    // Validation: c1 and c2 positive, c1 < c2\n    if (c1 <= 0 || c2 <= 0) {\n      alert(\"Constants c1 and c2 must be positive.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (c1 >= c2) {\n      alert(\"Constant c1 (lower bound) must be less than c2 (upper bound).\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const fits = drawUserFunction(a,b,c1,c2);\n    const resultText = document.getElementById(\"resultText\");\n    if (fits) {\n      resultText.textContent = `Yes! For sufficiently large n, f(n) = ${a}n + ${b} fits within the bounds ${c1}n ≤ f(n) ≤ ${c2}n, so f(n) = Θ(n).`;\n      resultText.style.color = \"#27ae60\";\n    } else {\n      resultText.textContent = `No, f(n) = ${a}n + ${b} does NOT stay within the bounds ${c1}n and ${c2}n for large n, so f(n) ≠ Θ(n) with these constants. Try different constants or function.`;\n      resultText.style.color = \"#c0392b\";\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Initial draw:\n  drawThetaExample();\n  drawUserFunction(3,5,2,4);\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
